article.description: — Dravon Mangum had 16 points as Radford defeated Campbell 97-91 in triple overtime on Tuesday night.
article.headline: Mangum leads Radford past Campbell 97-91 in 3OT
article.linkText: Mangum leads Radford past Campbell 97-91 in 3OT
article.story: BUIES CREEK, N.C. -- — Dravon Mangum had 16 points as Radford defeated Campbell 97-91 in triple overtime on Tuesday night. Fah’Mir Ali buried 3-pointers near the end of regulation to tie it forcing the first overtime and again near the end of the second overtime forcing a third. Josiah Jeffers and Lewis Djonkam added 15 points apiece for the Highlanders. Djonkam also had nine rebounds. Shaquan Jules had 14 points for Radford (9-6, 8-1 Big South Conference), which won its fifth straight game. Jordan Whitfield scored a career-high 28 points for the Fighting Camels (8-8, 4-5). Cedric Henderson Jr. scored 18 points and Joshua Lusane scored 13 with 13 rebounds and five assists. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
